<H1><CENTER>ietf-ipsra mailing list</CENTER></H1>

<P>Welcome to the web site for the <B>ietf-ipsra</B> mailing list.
The ietf-ipsra mailing list is for the IPsec Remote Access Working Group
IETF. The group is discussing how to handle 
remote access users with changing IP addresses in IPsec.

<p>Everyone in the IPSRA WG should review
<a href="http://www.ietf.org/html.charters/ipsra-charter.html">the
Working Group's charter</a>.

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="1" NOSHADE></P>

<H2>Mailing List</H2>

<P>To subscribe to the mailing list, send a message to
<A HREF="mailto:ietf-ipsra-request@vpnc.org">ietf-ipsra-request@vpnc.org</A>
with the single word <B>subscribe</B> in the body of the message. To unsubscribe
from the list, use that same address with the single word <B>unsubscribe</B>
in the body of the message.</P>

<P>There is a <A HREF="mail-archive/">web-based archive</A> of the mailing
list.
You can also access the <A HREF="entire-arch.txt">entire archive</A>
as a text file.
Please read through the archive before posting to the mailing list, since
many topics of interest have already been discussed.</P>

<P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="1" NOSHADE></P>

<H2>Documents for the Mailing List</H2>

<P>Some documents being discussed on this mailing list are:</P>

<UL>
<li><a href="/draft-ietf-ipsra-pic">
PIC, A Pre-IKE Credential Provisioning Protocol</a>
(draft-ietf-ipsra-pic)
<li><a href="/rfc3457">
Requirements for IPsec Remote Access Scenarios</a>
(RFC 3457)
<LI><a href="/rfc3456">
Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCPv4) Configuration of IPsec
Tunnel Mode</a> (RFC 3456)

</UL>

